cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.CV

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on applying DRL to robotic applications and proposes a framework specifically tailored for local planning and navigation problems.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of DRL and proposes a novel framework for improving training efficiency.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely category as the paper deals with intelligent agents (robots) learning to perform tasks through reinforcement learning.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper discusses the use of a classical controller (PID) as an alternative policy to speed up training of DRL.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on visual perception or image processing, but it may still be relevant in the context of robotic navigation.
